5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to general contracting; to amend Section
10 34-8-7, Code of Alabama 1975, to provide additional services
11 to the list of exemptions to the requirements of the general
12 contracting law.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 34-8-7, Code of Alabama 1975, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 "§34-8-7
17 (a) The following shall be exempted from this chapter:
18 (1) The practice of general contracting, as defined in
19 Section 34-8-1, by an authorized representative of the United
20 States Government, the State of Alabama, or an incorporated
21 town, city, or county in this state, which is under the
22 supervision of a licensed architect or engineer, provided any
23 work contracted out by the authorized representative shall
24 comply with the definition in this chapter for general
25 contractor.
26 (2) The construction or repair of any residence or
27 private dwelling or any residential swimming pool.
28 (3) A person, firm, or corporation constructing a
