99 (c)(b) A subcontractor, as defined in Section
100 34-8-1(c), is subject to and shall comply with this chapter as
101 specified for a general contractor except as follows:
102 (1) A subcontractor shall pay one-half of the fees
103 required in this chapter for a general contractor.
104 (2) No bid limits shall be established for a
105 subcontractor.
106 (3) A subcontractor shall submit with license
107 application and renewals a statement of financial condition as
108 prescribed by the board.
109 (4) A subcontractor shall furnish three references from
110 any combination of the following: Licensed general
111 contractors, registered professional engineers, or registered
112 architects, or qualified person, as declared by the board, for
