113 whom they have worked. If a subcontractor has only been
114 employed by one company, the subcontractor shall provide the
115 following: Three or more jobs he or she has worked on, the
116 amounts of the contracts, the time period of the contracts,
117 the location of the contracts, and a statement of experience.
118 (5) A subcontractor is not required to be licensed at
119 the time a project is bid, but must be licensed with the board
120 prior to beginning work on the project.
121 (6) A general contractor license and license number
122 issued by the board to subcontractors shall denote
123 subcontractor status.
124 (7) A subcontractor is not required to sit for any
125 examination before being licensed."
